Prerequisite : Mysql-connector zip file

--> Integrating tomcat into eclipse:
	Window > Preferences > Server > Add > Apache Tomcat x.x > Browse to tomcat installation directory > Finish

--> Open a Dynamic web project > Next > Next > Generate web.xml deployment descriptor > Finish
--> Right click 'src' > new > servlet > Next > set URL-mapping tag 
--> Write servlet code > make entry into web.xml
--> Entry into web.xml : 
	 <servlet>
	  	<servlet-name>any_name</servlet-name>
	  	<servlet-class>Created class file name</servlet-class>
	  </servlet>
	  
	  <servlet-mapping>
	  	<servlet-name>any_name</servlet-name>
	  	<url-pattern>URL-mapping tag</url-pattern>
	  </servlet-mapping>
--> Deploying servlet:
	Right click on project > Run as > run on server > Manually define new server, tomcat x.x , server name localhost, > next > finish > 		Include URL-mapping tag in the URL 
